he given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":17,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":30,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":39,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Touchet III was born in 1298, in Ashwell, Rutland, England, his father, Sir Robert Touchet III - Lord of Ashwell, was 23 and his mother, Agnes d'Avesnes, was 19. He had at least 2 sons with Joan Tattenhall. He died on 18 August 1349, in Markeaton, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1298–18 August 1349":"1298–18. august 1349","1298–1349":"1298–1349","1302–1327":"1302–1327","1325–1367":"1325–1367","1327–1362":"1327–1362","1275–1337":"1275–1337","1279–1298":"1279–1298","about 1294":"umbes 1294","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","1327":"1327","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","25 July 1327":"25. juuli 1327","1302":"1302","1279":"1279","1367":"1367","18 August 1349":"18. august 1349","1453":"1453","1298":"1298","27 July 1327":"27. juuli 1327","1328":"13